def: An inciter or promoter of sedition. Bp. Hall.
A crystalline substance said to be found in the root of acertain plant of the Leadwort (Plumbago) family.
The act of resuscitating, or state of being resuscitated.The subject of resuscitation by his sorceries. Sir W. Scott.
A case for one several small articles; esp., a box in whichscissors, tweezers, and other articles of toilet or of daily use arecarried.
A man who lets horses and carriages for hire.
Having no albumen about the embryo; -- said of certain seeds.
The act of riding steeple chases.
